<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 30. Enicospilus nigribasalis (Uchida, 1928) ♀ from Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D head, lateral view E mesosoma, lateral view F central part of fore wing." , "Figure 46. Enicospilus signativentris (Tosquinet, 1903) ♀ from Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D head, lateral view E mesosoma, lateral view F central part of fore wing." , "Figure 40. Enicospilus riukiuensis (Matsumura & Uchida, 1926) ♀ from Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D head, lateral view E mesosoma, lateral view F central part of fore wing." , "Figure 4. Morphological terms and measurement characters for wings A fore wing (AC = anal cell, BC = basal cell, DS = discosubmarginal cell, FE = fenestra, FS = first subdiscal cell, FSM = fourth submarginal cell, MC = marginal cell, SD = second discal cell, SB = subbasal cell, SS = second subdiscal cell, TD = third discal cell) B hind wing (NI = mn / no, AC = anal cell, BC = basal cell, DC = discal cell, MC = marginal cell, SB = subbasal cell, SDC = subdiscal cell, SM = submarginal cell) C central part of fore wing (AI = cd / ab, CI = gf / fh, DI = k / fe, ICI = ab / bc, SDI = ef / gi, SI = l / j, SRI = ce / ef). Brown letters indicate veins and sclerites." , "Figure 41. Enicospilus sakaguchii (Matsumura & Uchida, 1926) ♀ from Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D head, lateral view E mesosoma, lateral view F central part of fore wing." , "Figure 19. Enicospilus insinuator (Smith, 1860) ♀ from Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D head, lateral view E mesosoma, lateral view F central part of fore wing." , "Figure 44. Enicospilus shikokuensis (Uchida, 1928) ♀ from Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D head, lateral view E mesosoma, lateral view F central part of fore wing." , "Figure 25. Enicospilus limnophilus Shimizu, sp. nov. ♀ (A-E HT F PT) from Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D head, lateral view E mesosoma, lateral view F central part of fore wing." , "Figure 36. Enicospilus pudibundae (Uchida, 1928) ♀ from Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D head, lateral view E mesosoma, lateral view F central part of fore wing." , "Figure 39. Enicospilus ramidulus (Linnaeus, 1758) ♀ from Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D head, lateral view E mesosoma, lateral view F central part of fore wing." , "Figure 5. Morphological terms and measurement characters for metasoma (DMI = e / f, PI = a / b, THI = c / d)." , "Figure 2. Morphological terms and measurement characters for head and mandible A head in frontal view (fh = face height, fw = face width, ch = clypeus height, cw = clypeus width) B head in lateral view (be = breadth of eye, bg = breadth of gena; GOI = be / bg) C mandible in outer view." , "Figure 50. Enicospilus unctus Shimizu, sp. nov. ♀ (HT) from Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D head, lateral view E mesosoma, lateral view F central part of fore wing." , "Figure 11. Enicospilus acutus Shimizu, sp. nov. ♀ from Japan (PT) A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D head, lateral view E mesosoma, lateral view F central part of fore wing." , "Figure 38. Enicospilus pungens (Smith, 1874) ♀ from Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D head, lateral view E mesosoma, lateral view F central part of fore wing." , "Figure 3. Morphological terms for mesosoma A lateral view B dorsal view." , "Figure 47. Enicospilus stenophleps Cushman, 1937 ♀ from Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D head, lateral view E mesosoma, lateral view F central part of fore wing." , "Figure 31. Enicospilus nigristigma Cushman, 1937 ♀ from Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D head, lateral view E mesosoma, lateral view F central part of fore wing." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473797" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473804" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473791" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473768" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473805" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473777" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473771" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473812" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473802" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473813" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473785" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473796" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473816" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473769" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473810" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473770" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473806" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/473807" .

